Since this is a GitHub repository, you can sync changes between your two laptops using Git. Here's the workflow:

On your second laptop:

Clone the repository (one-time setup):
git clone https://github.com/anthony1518/miliary-life-life-as-a-soldier.git
cd miliary-life-life-as-a-soldier

Make changes to the files

Save them to GitHub:
git add .
git commit -m "Description of changes"
git push

On your main laptop (this one):

Pull the changes from GitHub:
git pull

Key points:

Always git pull before starting work to get the latest changes
Always git push when done to save your work to GitHub
Use meaningful commit messages ("Fixed bug", "Updated game logic", etc.)
If both laptops have changes, Git will alert you to resolve conflicts before pushing
If you haven't set up Git on your second laptop yet, install it from git-scm.com, then follow the steps above.
